##Special Report | under the epidemic, can online education "go against the grain" ?

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

An epidemic has transformed the education industry, both as a period of social responsibility for online education companies and as an opportunity to prove its worth.

Reporter | Wang Yiyue, Deng Shuxia, Ye Yuchen, Wu Yangyang

Intern reporters | Tao Zidong, Yuan Ying

Editor | NI NI

Cartography

Summer and winter holidays have always been the peak season for educational institutions, but the current epidemic has changed the situation dramatically.

On January 27, the Ministry of Education issued a notice requesting that the 2020 spring semester be postponed, that students not go out at home, do not meet, do not hold and participate in intensive activities, and that training institutions cancel all kinds of offline courses. Seven days ago, all offline training institutions in Wuhan have been suspended.

"classes at New Oriental ground are all suspended, and one million students in winter vacation classes face no classes. If all classes are suspended and their fees refunded, New Oriental will have to close its doors and the livelihood of its eighty thousand old employees will become an immediate problem, " said Yu Minhong, founder of New Oriental, in his personal account.

However, on January 29, the Ministry of Education issued a "No suspension" call to encourage students to use various internet platforms for online learning. Traditional offline training institutions that have been hit hard are rushing to shift their business online. And winter vacation in the late period to the official back to school this period of time, is becoming a major online education platform to play a key stage.

Unlike many other industries that are likely to be severely affected by the epidemic, the current disaster offers new opportunities for online education to highlight its value. At the same time, however, companies in this field, as in any industry, will have to weather the emergency test.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
During the outbreak, a number of online education, online live broadcast platforms have played out the slogan "No suspension, no suspension" and provide teaching content.

Super Live

On January 22, Wuhan's Education Bureau, the epicenter of the outbreak, ordered primary and secondary schools to suspend all teaching activities and students'social activities during the winter break. Vice President Liu Renlei and other members of the management team had a hunch that Wuhan was about to see a surge of demand for online courses.

At 10 p.m. on January 23, the Wuhan Lihan corridor was closed and the city's public transport system was suspended. Liu Renlei and others quickly assembled a 50-person core team at midnight that day, concentrating on the heads of the product, technology, operation, customer service and teaching and research groups, to discuss options. After overnight preparations, on the morning of January 24, Youdao's online education platform Youdao Boutique class announced a donation of winter vacation live broadcast classes to the Wuhan area. Two days later, it was extended to the entire Hubei Province.

Soon, several online education platforms were also launching donations. New Oriental has donated 1 million New Oriental online spring classes to primary and secondary school users across the country, and Xueba has donated 10 million yuan to Hubei medical staff's children for the spring live small classes, 20,000 Hubei students to receive spring live streaming large class courses. In addition, a number of video platforms have set up a collection area, a collection of multiple education brand live channels, such as Kuaishou and who to learn, Viphid and more than 40 enterprises, in the APP sidebar on the launch of the "school suspension" zone.

The donated courses, which are basically winter or spring classes that have already started enrollment, are already available, but will be free of charge. "But when everyone started school later, the whole situation changed, " Liu told Yimagazine. Winter vacation to the end of the formal opening of the live courses, the focus has become and the school to do the transition and cooperation, usually wait for the beginning of the end.

In a top-of-the-line after the online free open-school live teacher classes, is based on this demand, the integration of a new set of courses. Most of the courses come from the original resource base, and the teaching and research team makes fine-tuning according to the pace and difficulty of the teaching progress in the school. In addition, in addition to the prepared content, a boutique class has also prepared some temporary "foreign" courses, such as invited the Chinese Medical Association member Bao Yunhua to explain the "teach you how to properly prevent COVID-19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Now Open A top-quality course will pop up the first page of the epidemic prevention and control curriculum recommendations.

"We are not going to replace the public schools, " Liu said. "Our orientation is to review, consolidate and improve, and supplement the in-class education so that in the future, the school can resume classes more smoothly. ". There is a top-quality course covering programming, mathematical thinking and other children stage quality courses, for K12 stage, it is focused on a knowledge point of thematic courses, from February 10 every day in the afternoon of a core course.

Other online education platforms focus on further "seamless integration" with schools.

At noon on January 25, it took only 26 hours from the decision-making stage to the entrance of the Spring Gas Station program, but the whole product went through three iterations. On Feb. 2, the assignments team released a free, live-streaming schedule for K12's main subjects for all grades, from 8 a.m. to 5:40 p.m. , every 40 minutes, with little difference from the school schedule. At the same time, Xueersi school and the Simian Tutor also chose the all-weather free in-school synchronous live lesson.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"In order to keep pace with the normal progress of the school, the pace, difficulty and length of classes are in line with the school, the classes are arranged according to the syllabus of the Ministry of Education, and eye-care exercises and indoor exercises are also included during class breaks, " the homework team said in a written response to Yimagazine. Mathematics and physics are divided into three levels, namely, synchronization, difficulty and competition, for students of different levels to choose from. In the evening master class, the tutorial shows Ji Lianhai, Munman, and other famous teachers.

On February 1, Xueersi school took the lead in the trial operation. Click on the free course entrance at the top of the APP home page to enter the course schedule and select courses to watch directly. On February 3, the class started with the help of Simian tutorial and homework. After users register, they need to purchase the class with 0 yuan according to their grade, and then enter the free course broadcasting room through the purchased class. Both of them will be able to receive the e-learning materials and review the course content 24 hours ago.

Unbearable traffic

Zhang Rong's daughter, who is in fourth grade at a Beijing Primary School, had planned to sign up for an offline class called Sipeiyou and a foreign English teacher during the winter break because the outbreak had thrown off the pace. During the winter vacation, she saw reposts of various lesson plans on her friends'circle, and a teacher at her daughter's school suggested trying live streaming classes online, so Zhang enrolled her child in a free live streaming class for ape tutoring.

On the day of the broadcast, Zhang Rong and her daughter got ready for class early and sat down in front of the IPAD before 1 p.m. The first class was the opening ceremony, and her studio quickly surpassed 800 people. However, three or four minutes later, the live broadcast suddenly can not show, the page has been in the loading state, online number fell to 70, Zhang Rong had to give up trying temporarily.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the afternoon of February 3, a student in Baoding also tweeted that he could not watch the live broadcast from the APE tutorial.

More than 5 million people were online on the same day, and the huge number of online users caused some of the live streaming rooms to fail, ape guidance said in a statement. After 14:00, the live feed is back to normal.

In order to ensure the continuity of teaching and listening, online education is inherently more stable to the technical system, but such a large-scale, short-term influx of traffic is the first time in history. On the first day alone, homework helped 1.5 million more people sign up for free live classes. Four days after it opened, 470,000 people have applied for a free live streaming course for a total of 190,000 classes. According to Netease Technology, the top online education brands enrolled about 2 million students over the summer in 2019.

"there is a lot of demand from kids for simultaneous learning, " said Zhang. "Free Live streaming is good in itself, and it would be better if the technology was stable. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Most of the school teachers who have no experience with live streaming are in the studio with their cell phones pointed at the textbook and drawing a circle around it. Yang Bing, a math teacher at Zhumadian's No. 4 Middle School, became an instant Internet sensation after she took a class live on the toilet. He said he didn't do it on purpose, but because it was quiet the students could hear the explanation.

The same is true for companies that provide online services to offline educational institutions.

"since the third day of the Lunar New Year, the number of registrations on our platform has increased several times a day, " said Fan Xiaoxing, COO of Gosling Communications, which surprised her.

Gosling is a technology service provider that provides Saas  , Paas, traffic, and ecological services to the education industry. One of its businesses is helping educational institutions implement live online teaching. According to Fan Xiaoxing's past experience, around the Spring Festival is the off-season for signing contracts, the day before the New Year's Eve the company has a holiday, leaving only a small number of staff on duty to maintain the platform operation.

However, from the beginning of the New Year, staff found that the platform's new user registration began to soar, customer service staff also continue to receive information.

At first, many clients wanted content on public interest topics such as how to care for a baby and how to adjust to the state of mind during an outbreak. As the epidemic progressed, many traditional offline educational institutions struggled to resume classes, they began asking Gosling for advice on how to create online courses, especially adult self exams and time-limited classes like the toefl ielts. And this demand, not only limited to Hubei, Shandong, Zhejiang, Jiangxi and other provinces registration volume has also appeared explosive growth. Gosling several key members to discuss the decision to launch an emergency plan to mobilize the team ahead of schedule.

Just processing these "find me" orders, gosling through the workload has been saturated. "There's a lot of buzz about signing contracts every day, " one employee told First Finance magazine Yimagazine.

For the company, simply teaching teachers how to use the platform is a major undertaking. To this end, Gosling co-founder Yu Qianli when his own anchor, opened an "education institutions to build an online classroom Faq 20 lectures, " Live for the consultant.

The speed at which the product will land will have to be dramatically shortened, as it used to take clients a month or three to get from pre consultation to final course delivery, and now it takes them a day or two to complete.

Since the third day of the Lunar New Year, Gosling Tong's core staff will hold a summary Meeting every night to summarize the business progress of the day, more than 100 people on the front line work until 11 p.m. -- the peak of the live streaming session -- starting at 8 p.m. GOSLING staff is still in the remote work state, because many people did not take home computer, the company even temporarily urgent purchase of a batch of computers sent to the staff, to facilitate their work.

Wing Gull Education, which focuses on the development and operation of "online classroom" products, has nearly 3,000 institutions registered in its core product, "ClassIn online classroom" , under the heading of "Foshan" . But with the influx of offline education providers, ClassIn's existing network is struggling to keep up. To this end, the company emergency overtime, the system capacity nearly 20 times, the result has led to a sharp decline in system stability, had to limit the flow again. The expanded system, Wing Gull explained in an open letter, will take a few days to stabilize.

The unbearable traffic test continues

Over the course of a week, goslings were exposed to more nuanced teaching scenarios, many of which they had never encountered before. "Our modular tools are relatively abundant in the industry. In the past two days, we have also discovered some special niche customer needs. For example, people who do painting education want to Connect Mai Chuan Tu, but we can not meet them for the time being. At this stage, we are focusing on protecting the needs of the general public, " Fan said, "We've been interviewing people online these days, and we're looking for people ahead of time. "

Unlike many other platforms in the industry, which use the word "free" to further promote their customers, gotone's management, after some deliberation, decided to keep its price as a "lock-in" for older customers, also provides the stable quality of service for the platform to provide the safeguard.

"Many customers care more about the platform's richness and quality of service than the price, " Fan said. Gosling also subsidizes the use of third-party resources, such as cloud storage.

According to the traffic calculation of GOSLING's platform, most users are still at the stage of preparing to go online. For how long can the surge of orders caused by the epidemic last, and how much can be left after classes resume offline, fan Xiaoxing appears to be quite cautious: "At present to do or good customer service. "

During the outbreak, Hao fuwei group, which offers free live-streaming classes through Xueersi, also told China business news that it is still in the pilot phase and "the volume is really big and there are a lot of issues to deal with. " As planned, online education platforms are adding extra pressure to temporarily increase the number of simultaneous live-streaming classes in schools during winter break classes and spring enrollment. Ape Coach said it has deployed 356 lecturers, 412 teaching assistants and 151 technicians to participate in the free super live program. If the company's donation limited to the Hubei region, but also a lot of manpower to do the identity verification of students.

With the first wave of classes, many online education companies did attract a large number of free users with their products. The high cost of acquiring customers has been a sore point for the online education industry. According to data released by Netease Technology, the average cost of online education companies is as high as 1000 yuan, the industry conversion rate in 20% to 30% .

But it is hard to measure the efficiency of the surge in traffic that eventually translates into paying customers. After all, free streaming doesn't get the same amount of attention and supervision as a class, and learning effectiveness is more dependent on students'self-awareness and learning habits.

The trials continue. On 17 February, primary and secondary schools across the country began to resume classes, although the Ministry of Education said on 4 February that local primary and secondary schools and educational training institutions should not offer online instruction for the new semester before the formal start of the school year, but many schools are already offering online instruction in advance of resuming classes offline. This is both a great opportunity and an even greater challenge for the online education industry, which has long craved to penetrate into on-campus time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are already a number of online education companies working with these public schools. Good Future, for example, as of January 30, it had received requests from nearly 200 schools across the country, opening a total of 66 schools for platform testing. After the demand docking, the good future will train teachers on-line, production manual, teachers in the computer to download a good future live cloud software live teaching, students can be at home through computers, mobile phones, tablets and other devices. Like its Webschool, the software also offers tools such as answer machines.

Primary and secondary schools in Zhengzhou, Henan Province, uniformly use nail nail, an online office software owned by Alibaba. At the end of December 2019, nail emergency online support for multi-person audio-video conferencing system, free support for 102 simultaneous audio-video conferencing. This feature is no doubt being developed as a matter of urgency in response to the demands of the epidemic, but the target group of 102 people may not be office workers but classrooms.

On Feb. 1, Chen Yan, a high school senior at Xinzheng No. 3 Middle School in Zhengzhou, used the APP to teach a class to 50 students in her class. All the students had audio on, and she turned on the camera by herself, feeling no different than usual, except that she had to constantly switch between a powerpoint presentation and a live feed. Classes at Chen Yan's school are scheduled at the same pace as in the morning and afternoon, with breaks stretching from 10 minutes to half an hour. No classes are scheduled in the evening, but they are still read early in the morning.

"Class Teachers and Chinese and English teachers will regularly enter wechat groups in the morning to do student roll-calling, and parents will make videos to upload and supervise students to read early, " Chen Yan said, but such supervision is limited.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Nail, however, received a star of "rage" from the students and teachers who were yanked back to their desks.

In March 2019, nail launched a "education nail" for the education industry, the Ministry of Education in December of that year, the same month won the population of Zhengzhou Education Bureau "order. Among them, the Education Bureau of Zhengzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone requires all educational units in the region to register and activate the "nail wisdom education platform" by January 19, through this platform, educational units will release "official information" for their subordinate educational system. The district also plans to complete after February 10 class groups, parents of information into the formation of "Home School Directory. ".

This means that once the platform is deployed on a large scale on February 10th, the system's stability is likely to be of even greater concern -- as if public schools and their students'parents don't have a high tolerance rate.

In fact, more schools do not choose these market-oriented online education platform. For example, Wuhan Primary and secondary schools use the air classroom platform, the developers of Wuhan Tianyu Information Industry Co. , Ltd. . It includes live teaching, Interactive question-and-answer, on-demand review, homework, exams and other functions. Live teaching in primary and junior high schools is taught by teachers from all districts, while in senior high schools each school teaches its own lessons. Primary and secondary schools in Changsha, Hunan Province, are offering online courses on a platform called Renrentong, which is supported by Day Day Up. Both companies have an endorsement from the Department of Education.

In Beijing and other places, many schools choose to develop their own system, by the school or District Education Committee unified arrangements in advance recording. For example, the 80th High School in Chaoyang District launched its own online class system in 2015, when Beijing's smog reached a high level of pollution. Today, teachers are skilled at using a computer at home, recording classes on a screen -- in fact, 17 years ago, during the SARS epidemic, the Beijing area also opened an "air class" , in the form of video lectures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"classroom in the air" during SARS period

Tsinghua uses its own "rain class" platform, which supports online delivery of moocs (large open online courses) , handwritten video screens, other videos, voice, powerpoint presentations and problem sets. "Rain Class" is not limited to the Tsinghua School, many other schools are also using.

"We don't recommend any other online education to students, " a teacher at No.80 High School of Beijing told Yimagazine. "If you have an online course in your school, you will definitely give priority to your own course, which is more in line with the actual situation of the students and the academic situation. ".
